'''Nedim Imaç''' (born 1966 in [[The Hague]] - died February 17, 2007 in [[Amsterdam]]) was a [[Turkish people|Turkish]]-[[Netherlands|Dutch]] businessman and sports executive. He was the former chairman of the Amsterdam football club [[FC Türkiyemspor|Türkiyemspor]] and a prominent face of the [[Turks in the Netherlands|Turkish community in the Netherlands]]. He was also one of the important leaders of the Turkish [[heroin]] [[organized crime|mafia]] in the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web |author=NRC|title=De laatste wedstrijd voor integratievoetbal|url=http://www.nrc.nl/binnenland/article2161255.ece/De_laatste_wedstrijd_voor_integratievoetbal|accessdate=2010-08-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Parool|title=Derde verdachte moord Imaç|url=http://www.parool.nl/parool/nl/7/Misdaad/article/detail/35057/2008/10/02/Derde-verdachte-moord-Imac.dhtml|accessdate=2010-08-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Sabah|title=Hollanda'da Türk'e mafya infazı|url=http://arsiv.sabah.com.tr/2007/02/19/gun134.html|accessdate=2010-08-07}}</ref>
