The '''Teleport''' is a suburban-style 100-acre [[business park]] east of [[New York State Route 440]] and west of the [[Bulls Head, Staten Island|Bulls Head]] neighborhood on [[Staten Island]] in [[New York City]]. It includes five Class A office and specialized buildings totaling 700,000 square feet, as well as additional development-ready sites.<ref>{{cite web | title = The Teleport | publisher = PANYNJ | date = | url = http://www.panynj.gov/real-estate-development/teleport.html | accessdate = 2014-12-23}}</ref>
The Teleport was developed in the mid-1980s by the City of New York and the [[Port Authority of New York and New Jersey]] (PANYNJ), which manages it under contract to the city, focusing on new technologies and offering high-speed voice, data and video services via satellite and fiber optic connectivity.<ref>McCain, Mark. [https://www.nytimes.com/1988/01/03/realestate/commercial-property-teleport-moving-ahead-off-beaten-path-staten-island.html "Commercial Property: The Teleport; Moving Ahead Off the Beaten Path in Staten Island"], ''[[The New York Times]]'', January 3, 1988. Accessed June 3, 2009.</ref>
In 2001 [[AT&T]], the Teleport's biggest tenant, moved 4,000 employees out of two office buildings on the site.<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title = A new era for Staten Island's Teleport: City EDC initiative holds promise of jobs and financial growth | publisher = Staten Island Advance | date = July 25, 2013 | url = http://www.silive.com/opinion/index.ssf/2013/07/a_new_era_for_staten_islands_t.html | accessdate = 2014-12-23}}</ref> They were sold in 2009 to the Nicotra Group, LLC and renamed Corporate Commons,<ref>{{cite web|author=Advance file photo |url=http://www.silive.com/news/index.ssf/2008/12/staten_island_hoteliers_develo.html |title=Staten Island hoteliers, developers purchase 2 Teleport buildings |publisher=SILive.com |date=2008-12-03 |accessdate=2016-03-28}}</ref> with a major tenant being the St Paul's School of Nursing.<ref>{{cite web|author=Advance photo/Jan Somma-Hammel |url=http://www.silive.com/westshore/index.ssf/2009/06/first_tenant_set_for_staten_is.html |title=First tenant set for Staten Island's Corporate Commons |publisher=SILive.com |date= |accessdate=2016-03-28}}</ref>
The [[New York City Economic Development Corporation]] and the PANYNJ retain control over the available development acreage.<ref>{{cite press release | title = NYCEDC Seeks Expressions of Interest For Development at the Teleport on Staten Island | publisher = NYCEDC | date = July 18, 2013 | url = http://www.nycedc.com/press-release/nycedc-seeks-expressions-interest-development-teleport-staten-island | accessdate = 2014-12-23}}</ref>
