'''Terry Budge ''' is an [[Australia]]n banking executive and the [[Chancellor]] of [[Murdoch University]], which is located in the suburb of [[Murdoch, Western Australia|Murdoch]], [[Western Australia]].<ref name="Aspen">{{cite web |url=http://www.aspengroup.com.au/about_aspen/directors.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-05-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100521044634/http://www.aspengroup.com.au/about_aspen/directors.html |archivedate=21 May 2010 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.leadershipwa.org.au/html/whoweare_TBudge.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-05-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091013093726/http://www.leadershipwa.org.au/html/whoweare_TBudge.htm |archivedate=13 October 2009 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>

==History==
Terry Budge started his career as a banker with over 35 years in the Australian banking sector and business. He was the Managing Director of [[Bankwest]] from 1997 to 2004 and worked with the [[National Australia Bank]] for 25 years in various senior executive positions.<ref name="Aspen"/>

Budge is the Chairman of Leadership WA, Chancellor of [[Murdoch University]], directorship of Westoz Investment Company and Days of Change,<ref>[http://daysofchange.org/about/the-team.aspx daysofchange.org profile]</ref> and is a director of [[Aon (company)|AON Risk Services]] Australia Board of Advice.<ref name="mu">{{cite web |url=http://senate.murdoch.edu.au/members/budge.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-05-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110218152414/http://senate.murdoch.edu.au/members/budge.html |archivedate=18 February 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>

Budge’s former positions included Chairman of [[LandCorp]], National Director and Western Australian State President of the [[Australian Institute of Company Directors]], the State President of the [[Committee for Economic Development of Australia]] and director of the [[Government of Australia|Federal Government's]] Financial Sector Advisory Council.<ref name="mu"/>

He was appointed chancellor of Murdoch University in late 2006.<ref name="mu"/>

